description.originalText: Vanessa is amazing!  She has helped watch my toddler now that I have a newborn and my toddler loves her!  She helps keep her entertained for hours, playing with her toys, going to parks or out on adventures.  She is so engaging and very perceptive as well.  My toddler has been having a hard time adjusting to life with a sister, and Vanessa has been so patient with her as she helps her navigate her big feelings as well.  Iâ€™m so thankful for all of her help and expertise with little ones!

Vanessa is an exceptional nanny. She first started as our part time nanny back in February and then began full time for the summer where she watched my daughters, ages 4 and 2. She not only has a strong unique bond with both of my daughters, where they respect her and find her so engaging and fun, but she also is very professional and dedicated and shows she truly cares for us as a family. She is punctual, ensures the kids eat healthy throughout the day, keeps them on schedule and is meticulous about keeping their space, toys, and books in order. She arrives daily with a smile on her face and is so pleasant to be around. We all look forward to seeing her everyday.

description.displayText: Vanessa started with us when my son was about 3 months old. We are relocating in June and that is the only reason why she will be available again. Vanessa is an amazing nanny. She is kind and nurturing, energetic and loving and really treats our son like he is her own.  She takes excellent care of him and has taught me a lot.  Our son absolutely adores her (as do we!) She is extremely engaged with him. She teaches him Spanish, she sings and reads to him, takes him to classes, helps him reach developmental milestones, handles his food prep, laundry etc. We would recommend her to anyone, and are truly sad to part with her. Don't pass on Vanessa, she is very special!

description.displayText:
Vanessa is an amazing, unique, and differentiated nanny who far exceeds other nannies that we have met. Apart from being amazing with kids, she is also educated and intelligent.

Vanessa has cared for our son since he was 9 months old. She speaks to him in both English and Spanish. We love that she is so energetic, fun, warmhearted, and loving. We ask her to take lots of photos and videos of our son, and she does a great job with that. She has enrolled our son in different classes on her own. She is very independent and is mindful of milestones he should be meeting. She keeps to a tight schedule, cooks healthy meals, cleans, and does his laundry while he naps. She is basically his surrogate mother as we both work long hours. She even stayed at our apartment and cared for our son while we were out of the country for 2 weeks. Our son got sick while we were away, but she know what to do to care for him and put our mind at ease despite how far away we were. We trust her above and beyond.

description.displayText: Vanessa was great! My son immediately accepted her and wanted to show her all of his toys (he's 2 years old). The weather was terrible so they were stuck inside all day but Vanessa kept him busy doing arts and crafts, dancing and just running around. She was punctual and communicative about the day and what they did. I have already hired her to watch my son again. Highly recommend Vanessa to any family.

Our girls love her and look forward to seeing Vanessa. Vanessa is part of our family and we couldn't imagine our lives without her. Our girls feel the same way. Vanessa is very helpful in all ways and will always take the extra mile to help in any way!!! Please contact me if you have any other questions!!!
